snippet.textDisplay:
Replacing all the seals on that backhoe is a fairly easy task. The first one may give you a fit, but after that you'll have it down.
If the collar to hold the ram is smooth and female. Smack it with a hammer for 30 secs or more rotating. It should come off pretty easy. Dont hit the cylinder as you could damage it making any seals you put in wear faster.
If the rams are like CATs if you dont want to buy the spanner, just weld some bar stock on the cap and use a hammer or cheater pipe to turn it off. CASE are about the same as CAT. I'm not familiar with JCB stuff.
snippet.textOriginal:

If the rams are like CATs if you dont want to buy the spanner, just weld some bar stock on the cap and use a hammer or cheater pipe to turn it off. CASE are about the same as CAT.  I'm not familiar with JCB stuff.

snippet.textDisplay: I run a few different tow trucks, one of them you have to put the parking brake on, leave it in neutral, and you can set the RPMs to 1,250 (through cruise control) and that's where you want the PTO on at.
